The paper discusses anonymization techniques for tabular datasets, which are commonly used in databases and data mining. This suggests that it could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CY (Computers and Society), or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). However, since the focus is on privacy and risk assessment, cs.CR is the most likely category. cs.DB is also a likely category since the paper deals with data management and manipulation. cs.LG and cs.IR are less likely since they are more focused on machine learning and information retrieval, respectively, and may not be as relevant to the topic of anonymization. cs.CY is also a possibility since it deals with the intersection of computers and society, which includes privacy concerns.
